      • MLUser

        public MLUser()
        Constructs a new MLUser with no data in it. A MLUser constructed in this way will not have an objectId and will not persist to the database until MLUserManager.signUp() is called.

      • getCurrentUser

        public static MLUser getCurrentUser()
        This retrieves the currently logged in MLUser with a valid session, either from memory or disk if necessary.
        返回:
        The currently logged in MLUser.

      • logOut

        public static void logOut()
        Logs out the currently logged in user session. This will remove the session from disk, log out of linked services, and future calls to MLUser.getCurrentUser() will return null.

      • isAuthenticated

        public boolean isAuthenticated()
        Whether the MLUser has been authenticated on this device. This will be true if the MLUser was obtained via a loginInBackground or signUp method. Only an authenticated MLUser can be saved (with altered attributes) and deleted.
        返回:
        isAuthenticated
